Johannesburg At least two prisoners were in critical condition after a fire broke out at Leeuwkop Prison north of Johannesburg on Friday, paramedics said. Netcare911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said a total of 36 have sustained serious to minor injuries. &quot;Netcare911 paramedics are on scene with various emergency services. Paramedics are busy treating the prisoners for smoke inhalation and burn wounds,&quot; she said. &quot;Those who require further medical care will be transported to various hospitals in Johannesburg for further medical care.&quot; African News Agency